A. It is now almost the time when we should<lb/>
perceive the dawning of the eastern light, but<lb/>
from those heavy clouds, which obscure the<lb/>
whole of our horizon &amp; from the long continued<lb/>
&amp; dead stillness of the mountain I suspect<lb/>
that we are on the eve of some great change<lb/>
and a storm, if not an eruption is approaching<lb/>
so that I think it will be prudent for us to<lb/>
return to <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
