under the same brillant &amp; beautiful circumstances.<lb/>
but the storm which you augured does not yet<lb/>
fall, and there is a peculiar heat in the air and<lb/>
the sea tho' there is no breath of wind seems to<lb/>
roll waves almost as black as pitch from<lb/>
the reflexion of the sky towards the shore<lb/>
A. Surely I felt at that moment a motion of the<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
