of an earthquake.<lb/>
All. We felt it.<lb/>
A. Watch the mountain, See the pitchy cloud<lb/>
on the top of it bursts open &amp; a column of <lb/>
flames, &amp; a jet of lava &amp; red hot stones rises<lb/>
into the middle heaven! The ground again<lb/>
shakes &amp; lo! The tremendous thunder of an<lb/>
eruption!<lb/>
P. Lo' The lava bursts forth from the top,<lb/>
&amp; watch the skies filled with flame! A<lb/>
river of fire descends to the earth! I <lb/>
give you joy. Archteus that the wish which<lb/>
you have so long indulged is gratified, &amp;<lb/>
that you will have an opportunity of ex-<lb/>
