            <lb/>
of heat in communication and afterwars I shall endeavour<lb/>
to describe the phaenomena presented by its radiation<lb/>
Heat is communicated from body to body but with<lb/>
very different degrees of velocity; those that transmit it<lb/>
with the greatest quickness are called good conductors<lb/>
of heat, metals are amongst the best conductors, metal<lb/>
-lic oxyds, <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
