Amidst the variety of researches which<lb/>
have been pursued respecting the different<lb/>
forms &amp; modes of excitation and action<lb/>
of Electricity, it is surprizing to me that<lb/>
the Electricity of living animals has<lb/>
not been more an object of attention,<lb/>
both on account of its physiological<lb/>
importance of its general relation<lb/>
 to the science of Electro-Chemistry.<lb/>
